Hi Alfredo,

We don't have an msi file, only an exe and a script.
Please find an archived .vbs file in the below link, for the silent uninstall of the EPP Client on Windows: http://download.endpointprotector.com/debug_agent/epp_uninstall.zip

If you have an uninstall protection password, enter it in the uninstall_password line, according to the instructions, before running the .vbs. This tool is meant to be run via the command line or via a GPO and would be best to reboot the machines that have received the uninstall command.
